Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, suggesting non-diabetic glucosuria. These findings indicate impaired renal function, likely acute or chronic kidney disease with possible tubular dysfunction. Urinary findings may also suggest possible hepatic involvement or hemolysis. Prompt nephrology evaluation and further workup are recommended.
